body_html:
Thanks @case540 @yifeif for the help. It looks like the changes are already in though the PR is not closed automatically. When I do the git rebase upstream/master it have:

ubuntu@ip-172-31-47-125:~/tensorflow$ git rebase --continue
Applying: Fix Windows Build failures caused by os.path.join
No changes - did you forget to use 'git add'?
If there is nothing left to stage, chances are that something else
already introduced the same changes; you might want to skip this patch.

When you have resolved this problem, run "git rebase --continue".
If you prefer to skip this patch, run "git rebase --skip" instead.
To check out the original branch and stop rebasing, run "git rebase --abort".

ubuntu@ip-172-31-47-125:~/tensorflow$

I also checked the master and the changes are there. I think it is safe to close this PR.

```

Applying: Fix Windows Build failures caused by os.path.join
No changes - did you forget to use 'git add'?

already introduced the same changes; you might want to skip this patch.

When you have resolved this problem, run "git rebase --continue".
If you prefer to skip this patch, run "git rebase --skip" instead.
```

I also checked the master and the changes are there. I think it is safe to close this PR.
